# BROWSER-post.md - IH Post Creation Patterns

## Selectors

| Element | Selector | Notes |
|---------|----------|-------|
| Title field | `textarea.post-page__title-field` | maxlength=140, Ember textarea |
| Body field | `textarea.edit-post__body-field` | maxlength=100000, Ember textarea, supports Markdown |
| Group selector trigger | `.group-selector__trigger` | Click to open dropdown |
| Group selector collapsed | `.group-selector--collapsed` | Check before clicking |
| Submit button | `.post-page__submit-button` | Disabled until title+body filled |
| Save draft button | `.post-page__save-draft` | Always enabled |
| Preview toggle | `.post-page__preview-toggle` | |

## Notes
- Body is a plain `<textarea>` — use `.value` + input event
- Skip group selector — post to general feed

## S 7. Create and Submit Post

```bash
# Step 1: Set title (Ember textarea — use .value + input event)
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { var titleArea = document.querySelector('textarea.post-page__title-field'); if (!titleArea) return { error: 'title_field_not_found' }; titleArea.focus(); titleArea.value = '${postTitle}'; titleArea.dispatchEvent(new Event('input', { bubbles: true })); titleArea.dispatchEvent(new Event('change', { bubbles: true })); return { success: true, titleLen: titleArea.value.length }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

```bash
# Step 2: Set body (Ember textarea — use .value + input event)
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { var bodyArea = document.querySelector('textarea.edit-post__body-field'); if (!bodyArea) return { error: 'body_field_not_found' }; bodyArea.focus(); bodyArea.value = '${postBody}'; bodyArea.dispatchEvent(new Event('input', { bubbles: true })); bodyArea.dispatchEvent(new Event('change', { bubbles: true })); return { success: true, bodyLen: bodyArea.value.length }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

```bash
# Step 3: Wait 500ms for Ember state, then check + click submit
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500)); var submitBtn = document.querySelector('.post-page__submit-button'); if (!submitBtn) return { error: 'submit_button_not_found' }; if (submitBtn.disabled) return { error: 'submit_disabled', hint: 'title or body may be empty' }; submitBtn.click(); return { success: true }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

```bash
# Step 4: Wait 4s, verify URL changed from /new-post to /post/slug
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 4000)); return { url: location.href, isPublished: !location.href.includes('/new-post'), title: document.title }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

If `isPublished: false` after step 4: retry submit once. If still fails, return HEARTBEAT_BLOCKED.

## S 8. Dismiss Cookie Banner (if present)

Run once at browser startup, before any post interaction:

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { var acceptBtn = document.querySelector('#onetrust-accept-btn-handler'); if (acceptBtn) { acceptBtn.click(); return { dismissed: true }; } return { noBanner: true }; }"}
ENDJSON
```
